name: Indonesian Embassy in Vienna
text: On the topic of United Nations Security Council reform, Indonesia fully supports a more democratic, representative, and effective Security Council that reflects the current world realities and all regions equitably, as part of the broader United Nations reform. #Indonesia4UNSC

name: Indonesian Embassy in Vienna
text: participating in ten United Nations Peacekeeping Operations (ranks number 9), and Indonesia is keen to enhance its participation further by increasing the number of its personnel up to 4,000 peacekeepers by 2019.#Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner #ATruePartner4Peace

name: Indonesian Embassy in Vienna
text: Indonesia accords very high importance to the cause of United Nations peacekeeping, and has actively participated in the United Nations Peacekeeping Operations since 1957. Currently, there are around 2,700 Indonesian military and police personnel #Indonesia4UNSC #ATruePartner

name: Indonesian Embassy in Vienna
text: During its membership to the UN Security Council in previous years,Indonesia played its role as a moderating voice and as a bridge and consensus builder among the members of the Security Council and broader UN Member States on the issues under the purview of the Security Council.

name: Indonesian Embassy in Vienna
